and handle either version. counterfeiting[edit] counterfeiting is a serious problem. anyone staying in china for a few months would have certain experience on it. from ¥1 coin, to ¥10, ¥20, ¥50 and ¥100 bills, all currency are subject to a risk. the main focus is on the texture of different parts, metal line, change of colors under different lights. ask anyone how, all of them have their own way. one such strategy for bills is to hold it up to the light: all real bills will have a watermark in the white blank space off to the side. it is 